data.enText: strange and frightening; different from what you are used to

data.chText: 在一个突然变得陌生而危险的世界里，他是她唯一的守护神。
data.enText: In a world that had suddenly become alien and dangerous, he was her only security.
from another country or society; foreign

data.chText: 不相容；相抵触；格格不入
这种思想与我们的宗教不相容。
data.enText: The idea is alien to our religion.
Cruelty was quite alien to him.
connected with creatures from another world
a person who is not a citizen of the country in which they live or work

simple_means.memory_skill: al 其他的 + ien → 其他地方的 → 外国的

means: 〈诗〉疏远；离间；【法】(所有权的)让渡

ex.chText: 他们反对外国军队驻扎在该地区。
ex.enText: They were opposed to the presence of alien forces in the region.

ex.chText: 他曾对异域文化感兴趣。
ex.enText: He was interested in alien cultures.

synonyms.bx: 指属于另一个国家的，比 foreign 更正式，但没有 foreign 使用普遍，且常含贬义。

ex.chText: 我喜欢色彩鲜艳的异国花卉。
她更愿去有异国风情的地方旅行。
ex.enText: She prefers to travel to exotic places.

d.text: 来自异国的，外国情调的

ex.chText: 在国外居住多年之后，他回到了家。
ex.enText: After living in foreign countries for many years, he returned home.

ex.chText: 所有外国军队必须立即无条件地撤出。
ex.enText: All foreign troops must be withdrawn immediately and unconditionally.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，泛指来自他国的或与他国有关的。

ex.chText: 现在有很多外国留学生来中国学习汉语。
ex.enText: There are many overseas students now coming to China to study Chinese.

ex.chText: 该公司已经将更多的资金投入了海外市场。
ex.enText: The company has invested more money into its overseas market.

synonyms.bx: 指来自、存在于或发生在海外国家的，只作定语。

tr: a form of life assumed to exist outside the Earth or its atmosphere
a person who comes from a foreign country
someone who does not owe allegiance to your country
anyone who does not belong in the environment in which they are found
arouse hostility or indifference in where there had formerly been love, affection, or friendliness
example: She alienated her friends when she became fanatically religious
The will aliened the property to the heirs

tr: being or from or characteristic of another place or part of the world
not contained in or deriving from the essential nature of something
example: an economic theory alien to the spirit of capitalism
the mysticism so foreign to the French mind and temper
jealousy is foreign to her nature

value.def: Alien means belonging to a different country, race, or group, usually one you do not like or are frightened of.

example.ex: He said they were opposed to the presence of alien forces in the region.
example.tran: 他说他们反对外国军队驻扎在该地区。

value.def: You use alien to describe something that seems strange and perhaps frightening, because it is not part of your normal experience.

example.ex: His work offers an insight into an alien culture.
example.tran: 他的作品能让人们对一种异域文化产生较深入的了解。

value.def: If something is alien to you or to your normal feelings or behaviour, it is not the way you would normally feel or behave.

example.ex: Such an attitude is alien to most businessmen.
example.tran: 大多数商界人士都会对这样的态度感到陌生。

value.tran: 陌生的；格格不入的；不相容的

value.def: An alien is someone who is not a legal citizen of the country in which they live.

example.ex: Both women had hired illegal aliens for child care...
example.tran: 两个女人都曾雇过非法入境者照看孩子。

example.ex: When war broke out, he was interned as an enemy alien.
example.tran: 战争爆发时，他作为敌国人士遭到关押。

value.def: In science fiction, an alien is a creature from outer space.

trans: 异形丛生；异星虫群；异形虫群；异形群体
孤胆枪手；孤单枪手；异形杀手；异型打击者；孤胆
昆虫帝国；昆蟲帝國；虫豸帝国

rootsaffixes.indicate: = other, to change 其他的；改变状态
rootsaffixes.title: al, alter, altern

partsOfSpeech.dec: al 其他的；改变状态 + ias → 另外的名字）→ 化名
al 其他的；改变状态 + ien → 其他地方的 → 外国的
alien 外国的，外来的 + ate 做，造成，使… → 把别人当外来的人 → 疏远
alter 其他的；改变状态 + able 可…的 → 可改变的
alter 其他的；改变状态 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 改造，改变
altern 其他的；改变状态 + ate 做，造成，使… → 更换着做事 → 交替
altern 其他的；改变状态 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的，属于…的 → 交替〔选择的方法〕→ 二者择一
